node.text:
Looking to step up your movie snack game? I've got just the solution. 👌🏽 My Movie Night Snack Bars are the ultimate sweet and salty combo because why should you have to choose? They're easy to make and come together super quickly so the only difficult part is deciding what mix-ins to add. 🤔

Click here for the recipe 👉🏽 https://bit.ly/movienightsnack

node.text:
It was my birthday yesterday! I celebrated in the best way by caking up a storm because birthdays are really just natures way of telling us to eat more cake, right? 

Check out some of the birthday gifts I've caked up for myself over the years 👀 Any of them catch your eye?

PSST did you see everything on the HowToCakeIt website is on sale for up to 40% until the 28th! 

Now everyone can enjoy a bit of birthday fun 😉

When you unintentionally match your own SURPRISE birthday cake! 🥲  Talk about cake coordination 💁🏽‍♀️ 
My amazing coworkers surprised me with this gorgeous cake on set for my birthday today and now I have the perfect snack for watching the last episode of @crimesenekitchen tonight! 🙌🏽 I can't believe the Finale is tonight! Are you tuning in??

node.text:
This is why I ♥️ CAKE and all of the talented Bakers in our HowToCakeIt family 🤗
There are so many possibilities when it comes to the type of batter, decorations and overall style, the sky's the limit! 

Here we have:
• Joise's incredible Terrazzo Tile Flower Vase Cake with Nutella Chocolate Cake and Cookie Dough Filling
• Susanne's Novelty Chiffon Sushi Cake 
• Chelsey's gorgeous Vanilla Drip Cake

Comment down below which of the cakes is more your style! 🍰

node.text:
The quality of the ingredients I use when baking is EVERYTHING to me. It makes a huge difference in the end result. For these cute Tiramisu cups I tried out the ground Chameleon Organic Guatemala Coffee and I loved the bold flavor that came through! A great tiramisu NEEDS that hit! And so do I - does one (ok, maybe two) cups of tiramisu count towards my daily coffee intake? #RefuseToBlendIn

Ingredients:

Coffee soak:
• 1 ½ cups @chameleoncoffee ,cooled
• 1 Tbsp. Amaretto
• Pinch of kosher salt
• 1 Tbsp. white granulated sugar

Tiramisu filling:
• ⅓ cup granulated sugar
• 1 cup heavy whipping cream, cold
• ½ cup mascarpone, room temp. 
• 3 Lg egg yolks, room temp. 
• 24 ladyfinger cookies

Garnish:
• Crushed chocolate covered coffee beans
• Cocoa powder

Assembly:
• Whisk coffee, Amaretto, salt, & 1 Tbsp. sugar in a shallow dish until sugar and salt dissolve. Chill.
• Whisk cream and mascarpone in a medium bowl just until smooth. Set aside.
• Pour water in a large saucepan to come 2” up the sides; bring to a simmer. Combine egg yolks, remaining ⅓ cup sugar + 2 Tbsp. water in a medium heatproof bowl. Set bowl over the pan and reduce heat to low so water is at a bare simmer. Using an electric mixer, beat mixture on medium-high speed until egg yolks triple in volume and become pale yellow. The mixture should form a slowly dissolving ribbon when drizzled over itself in a bowl (this takes approx. 5-7 mins). Remove from heat.

• Using an electric mixer, beat cream and mascarpone in a large bowl until smooth, then on medium speed beat until medium peaks form.
• Add egg yolk mixture in 2 parts and gently fold until no streaks remain.
• Working one step at a time, dip ladyfingers into chilled coffee mixture and let soak just long enough for them to soften, 1-2 secs per side.
• Layout glasses and place a layer of cookies at the base (it’s okay to squish them). Dollop the filling to cover the cookies; repeat one more time. Cover & chill until firm, 6-12 hours (the longer the better).
• Serve with a light dusting of cocoa powder and crushed chocolate-covered coffee beans.

#ad #RefuseToBlendIn #ChameleonOrganicCoffee #chameleoncoffee #BringThatCraftHome #ChameleonColdBrew

node.text:
Muffins are basically miniature cakes already but I thought I'd take it to the next level by making my mega Blueberry Buttermilk Muffin Cake 😛 Now if only I'd managed to get that double egg crack 😔

You can find the recipe here 👉🏽 http://bit.ly/BlueberryMuffinCakeRecipe

Oh Bob, if only you'd been a bit more helpful in the kitchen I could have kept you around longer before devouring you 🤷🏽‍♀️ What a caking project this was though! Underneath that bright yellow fondant, and those sneaky gumpaste eyes is layers of moist chocolate cake, chocolate ganache, and Minion yellow buttercream 👌 Looks like I'm going to need a new little helper...

node.text:
It was my birthday yesterday! I celebrated in the best way by caking up a storm because birthdays are really just natures way of telling us to eat more cake, right? 

Check out some of the birthday gifts I've caked up for myself over the years 👀 Any of them catch your eye?

PSST did you see everything on the HowToCakeIt website is on sale for up to 40% until the 28th! 

Now everyone can enjoy a bit of birthday fun 😉

node.text: I've always thought Cakelings had a better ring to it... 🤔 Meet my Polly the panda Fingerlings cake! Complete with all the necessary appendages to hold onto Sir Squeeze of course 😉

I can't believe today is the LAST episode of @crimescenekitchen 🥺
This is definitely a bittersweet moment (pun intended) but I am so grateful for everyone who made the experience so amazing! 💓
I didn't get many behind the scenes photos from this episode because we shot for 18 hours on both days but it was well worth it because the finale tonight is going to be epic 🙌🏽
Who's tuning in at 9PM EST on Fox?!

node.text:
When you unintentionally match your own SURPRISE birthday cake! 🥲  Talk about cake coordination 💁🏽‍♀️ 
My amazing coworkers surprised me with this gorgeous cake on set for my birthday today and now I have the perfect snack for watching the last episode of @crimesenekitchen tonight! 🙌🏽 I can't believe the Finale is tonight! Are you tuning in??
